The paper discusses the use of machine learning in autonomous driving, specifically deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on motion planning, which is a key aspect of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of safety, which is a concern in systems and control (cs.SY).
